Possible because MAJOR dosn't support the forking so I couldn't fork junit test run like in this line:
<junit ... fork="yes" forkmode="once" .......> 

-----------------------------

Initially, I solved the regular junit test run when it wasn't able to run some test because it wasn't finding specific files by adding this line,
<junit ... fork="yes" forkmode="once" dir="./org.jacoco.core.test" .......>
